I never really tried to figure it out before.

568
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,680
Those gentlemen are men.

569
00:33:59,319 --> 00:34:00,559
Scholars can bring stability to the land.

570
00:34:00,559 --> 00:34:01,799
Martial artists can bring peace to the nation.

571
00:34:02,279 --> 00:34:03,680
They're all outstanding.

572
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:05,000
They're all talented people.

573
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:07,200
But how am I different from them?

574
00:34:08,119 --> 00:34:09,880
My father's wife and concubines were all women.

575
00:34:10,519 --> 00:34:12,159
They were dressed up so elegantly.

576
00:34:12,559 --> 00:34:13,880
He's got sideburns.

577
00:34:15,519 --> 00:34:17,719
Everyone's mind has changed.

578
00:34:18,519 --> 00:34:19,639
But what does that...

579
00:34:21,119 --> 00:34:22,400
have to do with me?

580
00:34:24,039 --> 00:34:25,039
Anyway,

581
00:34:25,809 --> 00:34:27,840
in the next few days, just stay here.

582
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:29,840
Don't go with them...

583
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,880
and let the cold wind blow on you out there.

584
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:34,880
This isn't right.

585
00:34:35,599 --> 00:34:36,809
You lied to me.

586
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:39,039
Your name must not be Shi Si Lang then.

587
00:34:39,639 --> 00:34:40,719
My name is Li Chang Ge.

588
00:34:41,559 --> 00:34:43,679
"Li Chang Ge".

589
00:34:46,809 --> 00:34:47,809
Then...

590
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:49,239
does Prince Sun...

591
00:34:49,519 --> 00:34:51,239
know about this?

592
00:34:54,079 --> 00:34:55,840
Then he has been hiding it all along.

593
00:34:56,559 --> 00:34:58,199
Could it be...

594
00:34:58,769 --> 00:35:00,329
that he has feelings for you?

595
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,920
What are you talking about?

596
00:35:04,079 --> 00:35:06,400
He just knows that I'm useful to him.

597
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:08,559
That's why he's a bit concerned about me.

598
00:35:12,079 --> 00:35:13,400
Are you feeling better?

599
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,679
It would feel better if you warm your stomach with it.

600
00:35:32,159 --> 00:35:33,920
What are you waiting for?

601
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,119
Move them.

602
00:35:35,360 --> 00:35:37,769
Moving wool is the simplest task.

603
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:42,769
Can you do it or not?

604
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,360
I can do it.

605
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,119
Why are you still standing there?

606
00:35:59,329 --> 00:36:00,559
Come and help me!

607
00:36:00,679 --> 00:36:02,000
- I'm coming. - Come on.

608
00:36:03,119 --> 00:36:04,119
It's all over the place.

609
00:36:04,769 --> 00:36:05,840
Here and here too.

610
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:07,480
- Get them off me. - There's another one here.

611
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,329
It's on your head too.

612
00:36:10,679 --> 00:36:11,840
You've got some here.

613
00:36:15,239 --> 00:36:16,360
Wool Yan Er!

614
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:17,960
- Wool Yan Er! - Wool Yan Er!

615
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,360
It's all over you.

616
00:36:20,119 --> 00:36:21,119
Li Wool Yan.

617
00:36:21,289 --> 00:36:22,440
Are you stupid?

618
00:36:22,639 --> 00:36:24,159
I just told you to move the wool. Look.

619
00:36:24,159 --> 00:36:25,719
You got it all over us.

620
00:36:25,719 --> 00:36:26,840
Madam Chai, I...

621
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:29,079
Look at your hair.

622
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:31,119
- Right. - My goodness.

623
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,519
Look at you.

624
00:36:48,119 --> 00:36:49,769
This little fool doesn't know how to do anything.

625
00:36:49,769 --> 00:36:52,239
- How is she still alive? - Exactly.

626
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:55,199
It's all thanks to you.

627
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:57,440
You're such precious people.

628
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,599
You saved me.

629
00:36:58,599 --> 00:37:00,519
That's why I'm still alive.

630
00:37:01,079 --> 00:37:02,599
This is the first time someone called me precious.

631
00:37:02,599 --> 00:37:03,769
Is she talking about you?

632
00:37:03,769 --> 00:37:05,159
Count your pay.

633
00:37:05,159 --> 00:37:06,360
You're not precious at all.

634
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,599
How is it not precious?

635
00:37:07,809 --> 00:37:09,239
Our wool clothing...

636
00:37:09,239 --> 00:37:11,289
is given as an offering to the prefecture offices.

637
00:37:11,289 --> 00:37:12,480
Perhaps...

638
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,639
they're even sent to the palace.

639
00:37:13,639 --> 00:37:15,880
Lichen clothing for the imperial family.

640
00:37:18,239 --> 00:37:19,880
You're working so hard.

641
00:37:21,119 --> 00:37:24,480
They might not cherish the clothing you made.

642
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:26,519
Why should we talk about this nonsense?

643
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:29,480
They were born without having to worry about making a living.

644
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:31,289
How would they know that behind their clothes,

645
00:37:31,289 --> 00:37:32,719
there are a lot of grievances?

646
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:35,719
God is fair.

647
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:37,199
The people in the palace...

648
00:37:37,199 --> 00:37:38,880
are being worshipped and fed by the citizens.

649
00:37:39,480 --> 00:37:41,679
They can get anything they want.

650
00:37:41,679 --> 00:37:42,920
So they must be responsible...

651
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:45,079
for the citizens.

652
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:46,599
As for us,

653
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:48,119
even though we're poor,

654
00:37:48,119 --> 00:37:49,329
we just need to fill our stomachs.

655
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:51,199
- Am I right? - Exactly.

656
00:37:51,199 --> 00:37:52,679
Let's just focus on ourselves...

657
00:37:52,809 --> 00:37:53,920
and do things right.

658
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,519
If we can't do things right, we just go to sleep.

659
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:58,039
If the imperial family can't do things right,

660
00:37:58,159 --> 00:37:59,840
can they fall asleep?

661
00:38:01,559 --> 00:38:02,719
We...

662
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:04,599
are just after our salary.

663
00:38:04,599 --> 00:38:05,599
Yes.

664
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:08,599
Do the work that you need to do.

665
00:38:09,159 --> 00:38:11,400
Don't run away once we mention our salaries, Madam Chai.

666
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:13,360
- Yes. When did we last get a raise? - Get back to work.

667
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:15,119
We're talking about salary. Don't run away.

668
00:38:15,119 --> 00:38:16,360
Let me talk to you about the salary.

669
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:18,519
If you won't increase our salary, at least buy some biscuits for us.

670
00:38:18,519 --> 00:38:20,360
- That's right. - Stop.

671
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:21,360
Don't run away.

672
00:38:26,289 --> 00:38:27,289
Stop.

673
00:38:45,079 --> 00:38:46,079
Le Yan.

674
00:38:46,809 --> 00:38:48,400
I must find you.

675
00:38:50,639 --> 00:38:51,639
Go!

676
00:38:54,199 --> 00:38:55,199
Go!

677
00:38:56,719 --> 00:38:57,719
Mimi.

678
00:38:58,079 --> 00:38:59,239
You're a woman.

679
00:38:59,239 --> 00:39:00,559
Don't work too hard.

680
00:39:00,559 --> 00:39:01,559
From now on,

681
00:39:01,719 --> 00:39:02,719
you can ask me to help you.

682
00:39:02,719 --> 00:39:03,960
I'll carry the water for you.

683
00:39:04,599 --> 00:39:06,679
Don't look down on me. I'm really incredible. Look.

684
00:39:08,329 --> 00:39:09,559
Be careful. My clothes...

685
00:39:09,559 --> 00:39:10,679
Don't let my clothes...

686
00:39:12,039 --> 00:39:13,289
What's wrong? Is it too heavy?

687
00:39:13,289 --> 00:39:14,400
No.

688
00:39:14,400 --> 00:39:15,400
My foot!

689
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,360
You're bleeding!

690
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:25,039
What rotten luck.

691
00:39:25,199 --> 00:39:27,199
Who threw away this nail?

692
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:30,840
I'm fine.

693
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:32,199
I'm just making a fuss because this rarely happens.

694
00:39:32,639 --> 00:39:33,639
Go ahead.

695
00:39:33,639 --> 00:39:34,920
I need a minute.

696
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,119
I'll bring you back.

697
00:39:39,119 --> 00:39:40,239
Let's leave the stuff here first.

698
00:39:41,599 --> 00:39:44,599
- Be careful. - I'm really all right. I'm fine.

699
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:49,440
Take it slow.

700
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:06,199
You've just recovered.

701
00:40:06,719 --> 00:40:07,840
Don't get sick again.

702
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:13,440
Don't worry. I'm not that weak.

703
00:40:15,039 --> 00:40:16,039
Keep it.

704
00:40:16,289 --> 00:40:17,480
You can wear it when you feel cold.

705
00:40:17,809 --> 00:40:19,199
You haven't accomplished anything yet.

706
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,289
I don't want to lose my investment.

707
00:40:22,769 --> 00:40:24,079
Don't worry, Your Highness.

708
00:40:24,079 --> 00:40:26,599
I'll surely accomplish the three things I promised you.

709
00:40:27,639 --> 00:40:29,519
Do you have any instructions for me today?

710
00:40:30,679 --> 00:40:31,840
I was making my rounds in the camp and I just passed by.

711
00:40:32,559 --> 00:40:33,559
All by yourself?

712
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:38,119
Where's that woman with you?

713
00:40:39,559 --> 00:40:40,719
She's doing laundry.

714
00:40:41,679 --> 00:40:42,809
She's lucky...

715
00:40:43,599 --> 00:40:44,769
to have you as her master.

716
00:40:45,289 --> 00:40:46,480
I'm not her master.

717
00:40:47,159 --> 00:40:48,880
We're friends who treasure each other.

718
00:40:49,880 --> 00:40:51,559
In life, the people around you...

719
00:40:51,559 --> 00:40:53,400
always leave one by one.

720
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,199
Trusting new people...

721
00:40:55,519 --> 00:40:56,639
and saying goodbye to old friends...

722
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:58,920
are all very difficult to do in life.

723
00:41:01,199 --> 00:41:02,840
Instead of saying that she's lucky,

724
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:03,960
consider me...

725
00:41:05,559 --> 00:41:06,719
the lucky one instead...

726
00:41:07,239 --> 00:41:09,039
for meeting someone I want to cherish.

727
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,480
Me too.

728
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:21,039
Go make your rounds, Your Highness.

729
00:41:21,039 --> 00:41:22,599
Otherwise, the sun will set soon.

730
00:41:24,329 --> 00:41:25,400
Why don't you join me?

731
00:41:25,809 --> 00:41:27,559
You haven't really gotten to know the grassland yet.

732
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,480
When it gets dark,

733
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,039
I'll take you somewhere.

734
00:41:31,719 --> 00:41:32,880
I just don't know if you'll dare.

735
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:34,639
Why wouldn't I?

736
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,039
It's so beautiful.

737
00:42:10,519 --> 00:42:12,159
I accidentally found this place when I was doing my rounds.

738
00:42:13,079 --> 00:42:14,079
Do you like it?

739
00:42:17,559 --> 00:42:18,809
This should be the last time...

740
00:42:18,809 --> 00:42:20,289
that we'd get to see fireflies this year.

741
00:42:21,239 --> 00:42:22,440
We'll get to see them again next year.

742
00:42:24,809 --> 00:42:26,719
Who knows where we'll be next year...

743
00:42:27,769 --> 00:42:30,000
and if we'd get a chance to see fireflies again?

744
00:42:31,719 --> 00:42:33,079
If you want to see them again next year,

745
00:42:34,480 --> 00:42:35,639
just let me know.

746
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:38,079
No matter where you are,

747
00:42:38,769 --> 00:42:39,920
I'll surely be there.

748
00:42:50,679 --> 00:42:52,079
I'm afraid I can't make it.

749
00:42:55,039 --> 00:42:57,960
Besides, beautiful things like fireflies...

750
00:42:57,960 --> 00:42:59,440
are fleeting.

751
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:01,360
So why look forward to them?

752
00:45:44,679 --> 00:45:49,760
(The Long Ballad)
